<EncodedData EncodedType="AddOnInstructionDefinition" Name="raC_Opr_HTTP_Client" Revision="1.3" RevisionExtension=".00" Vendor="Rockwell Automation" EditedDate="2025-03-11T09:39:44.715Z" SoftwareRevision="v34.03" EncryptionConfig="9">
<Description>
<![CDATA[HTTP Client to send REST requests to a server]]>
</Description>
<RevisionNote>
<![CDATA[Updated Cfg_UserAgent. Added Sts_MSGERR, Sts_MSGEXERR]]>
</RevisionNote>
<AdditionalHelpText>
<![CDATA[============================================================
Instruction Overview:
-----
raC_Opr_HTTP_Client instruction connects to a server and handles all the communications to send and receive HTTP commands. The client provides the following features/functionalities.

•	Send HTTP requests to the server.
•	Receives and parses HTTP responses from the server.
•	HTTP Version: 1.0.
•	Handles the connection management.
•	Supports the “connection: keep-alive “ and “connection: close” header.
•	Monitors the connection and gives status of the commands.
•	Supports custom header to be included in the request.
•	Parsing the response and store the results in a UDT to be easily used in Logix.
•	Support of multiple running instances to connect to different servers or to reduce the response time when multiple connections to the same server.
•	Support of multiple HTTP commands by using a command queue.



Instruction Execution:
-----
Level


Supplemental Descriptions:
-----
0	no error
1001	Unable to create socket. Refer Socket Create Message Error Code.
1002	Unable to connect to server. Refer Socket Open Connection Message Error Code.
1003	Failed to write. Refer Socket Write Message Error Code.
1004	Failed to read. Refer Socket Read Message Error Code.
1005	Read Timeout
1006	Error sending data
1007	Sequence Timeout. Increase Cfg_CmdTimeout if required.
2001	Invalid URL specified. Must start with http:// (case sensitive)
2002	Invalid Resource specified. Must start with ‘/’
2003	Custom Header too large
3001	Transfer-Encoding not supported
4001	No HTTP header found or malformed in response. Example no empty line
4002	HTTP Status was 1xx – Informational responses are not supported
4003	HTTP Status was 3xx – Redirections are not supported
4004	HTTP Status was 4xx – Client error
4005	HTTP Status was 5xx – Server error
4006	HTTP Status xxx – Unknown status code
4007	Transfer-Encoding is not supported


Revision Notes:
-----
1.3.00 - Updated Cfg_UserAgent
1.2.00 - Cmd_Initialize added
1.1.00 - Ref_Hndl.Sts_Initialized cleared in prescan
1.0.00 - Release


=============================================================== 

